ud6.10:2.2:
But when Tathāgatas–worthy & rightly self-awakened–appear in the world,
that’s when the wanderers of other sects are not worshipped, revered, honored, venerated, or given homage;
nor are they recipients of robes, alms food, lodgings, & medicinal requisites for the sick.

